er fourth US number-one single, \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just_Give_Me_a_Reason\">Just Give Me a Reason</a>\". In 2014, Pink recorded a collaborative album,&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rose_Ave._(album)\">Rose Ave.</a></em>, with Canadian musician&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dallas_Green_(musician)\">Dallas Green</a>&nbsp;under a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Folk_music\">folk music</a>&nbsp;duo named&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/You%2BMe\">You+Me</a>. Her next studio albums,&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beautiful_Trauma\">Beautiful Trauma</a></em>&nbsp;(2017) and&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hurts_2B_Human\">Hurts 2B Human</a></em>&nbsp;(2019), both debuted at atop the&nbsp;<em>Billboard</em>&nbsp;200 chart, with the former becoming the world\'s third best-selling album of the year.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Noted for her distinctive raspy voice and acrobatic stage presence, Pink has sold over 135 million records worldwide (60 million albums and 75 million singles), making her one of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_best-selling_music_artists\">world\'s best-selling music artists</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_awards_and_nominations_received_by_Pink\">Her accolades</a> include three <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammy_Awards\">Grammy Awards</a>, two <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brit_Awards\">Brit Awards</a>, a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daytime_Emmy_Award\">Daytime Emmy Award</a> and seven <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MTV_Video_Music_Award\">MTV Video Music Awards</a>, including the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Jackson_Video_Vanguard_Award\">Michael Jackson Video Vanguard Award</a>. In 2009, <em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billboard_(magazine)\">Billboard</a></em> named Pink the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mainstream_Top_40\">Pop Songs Artist of the Decade</a>. Pink was also the second most-played female solo artist in the United Kingdom during the 2000s decade, behind only <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madonna\">Madonna</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VH1\">VH1</a> ranked her at number ten on their list of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Greatest_(TV_series)\">100 Greatest Women in Music</a>, while <em>Billboard</em> awarded her the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billboard_Women_in_Music\">Woman of the Year</a> award in 2013. At the 63rd annual <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BMI_Award\">BMI Pop Awards</a>, she received the BMI President\'s Award for \"her outstanding achievement in songwriting and global impact on pop culture and the entertainment industry.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":25,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/pink3-1024x683.jpeg\" alt=\"Pink hanging from chandelier\" class=\"wp-image-25\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Wikipedia Contributors. “Pink (Singer).” <em>Wikipedia</em>, Wikimedia Foundation, 8 Feb. 2019, en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pink_(singer).</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->','P!NK','','inherit','closed','closed','','5-revision-v1','','','2022-07-09 09:33:58','2022-07-09 09:33:58','',5,'http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/?p=30',0,'revision','',0),
	(31,1,'2022-07-09 09:38:06','2022-07-09 09:38:06','<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":23,\"sizeSlug\":\"medium\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-medium\"><img src=\"http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/KevynAucoin3-183x300.jpeg\" alt=\"Kevyn and Cher\" class=\"wp-image-23\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Kevyn James Aucoin</strong> ( February 14, 1962 – May 7, 2002) was an American <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Make-up_artist\">make-up artist</a>, photographer and author. In the 1990s, Aucoin was wholly responsible for the \"sculpted\" look of many celebrities and top models, including <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whitney_Houston\">Whitney Houston</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cher\">Cher</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madonna_(entertainer)\">Madonna</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cindy_Crawford\">Cindy Crawford</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liza_Minnelli\">Liza Minnelli</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Courtney_Love\">Courtney Love</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tina_Turner\">Tina Turner</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Janet_Jackson\">Janet Jackson</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naomi_Campbell\">Naomi Campbell</a>, Tori Amos, and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vanessa_Williams\">Vanessa Williams</a>. He authored several industry-defining books with makeup techniques including facial <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contouring\">contouring</a>, which was relatively unknown in popular culture at the time, but pioneered and used in drag culture and stage makeup for decades prior. Aucoin, often noted as being decades ahead of his contemporaries, is considered to be one of greatest <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Make-up_artist\">make-up artists</a> of the modern age.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":22,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/KevynAucoin2.jpeg\" alt=\"Kevyn and Tina\" class=\"wp-image-22\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wikipedia Contributors. “Kevyn Aucoin.” <em>Wikipedia</em>, Wikimedia Foundation, 14 Dec. 2019, en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevyn_Aucoin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Kevyn Aucoin','','inherit','closed','closed','','15-autosave-v1','','','2022-07-09 09:38:06','2022-07-09 09:38:06','',15,'http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/?p=31',0,'revision','',0),
	(32,1,'2022-07-09 09:38:13','2022-07-09 09:38:13','<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":23,\"sizeSlug\":\"medium\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-medium\"><img src=\"http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/KevynAucoin3-183x300.jpeg\" alt=\"Kevyn and Cher\" class=\"wp-image-23\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Kevyn James Aucoin</strong> ( February 14, 1962 – May 7, 2002) was an American <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Make-up_artist\">make-up artist</a>, photographer and author. In the 1990s, Aucoin was wholly responsible for the \"sculpted\" look of many celebrities and top models, including <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whitney_Houston\">Whitney Houston</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cher\">Cher</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madonna_(entertainer)\">Madonna</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cindy_Crawford\">Cindy Crawford</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liza_Minnelli\">Liza Minnelli</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Courtney_Love\">Courtney Love</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tina_Turner\">Tina Turner</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Janet_Jackson\">Janet Jackson</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naomi_Campbell\">Naomi Campbell</a>, Tori Amos, and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vanessa_Williams\">Vanessa Williams</a>. He authored several industry-defining books with makeup techniques including facial <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contouring\">contouring</a>, which was relatively unknown in popular culture at the time, but pioneered and used in drag culture and stage makeup for decades prior. Aucoin, often noted as being decades ahead of his contemporaries, is considered to be one of greatest <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Make-up_artist\">make-up artists</a> of the modern age.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":22,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/KevynAucoin2.jpeg\" alt=\"Kevyn and Tina\" class=\"wp-image-22\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Wikipedia Contributors. “Kevyn Aucoin.” <em>Wikipedia</em>, Wikimedia Foundation, 14 Dec. 2019, en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevyn_Aucoin.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->','Kevyn Aucoin','','inherit','closed','closed','','15-revision-v1','','','2022-07-09 09:38:13','2022-07-09 09:38:13','',15,'http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/?p=32',0,'revision','',0),
	(33,1,'2022-07-09 09:40:56','2022-07-09 09:40:56','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Lee Alexander McQueen</strong> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Order_of_the_British_Empire\">CBE</a> (17 March 1969 – 11 February 2010) was a British <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fashion_designer\">fashion designer</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Couturier\">couturier</a>. He founded his own <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_McQueen_(brand)\">Alexander McQueen label</a> in 1992, and was chief designer at <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Givenchy\">Givenchy</a> from 1996 to 2001. His achievements in fashion earned him four <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Designer_of_the_Year\">British Designer of the Year</a> awards (1996, 1997, 2001 and 2003), as well as the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Fashion_Designers_of_America\">CFDA\'s</a> International Designer of the Year award in 2003.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":28,\"sizeSlug\":\"medium\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-medium\"><img src=\"http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Alexander3-300x300.jpeg\" alt=\"Alexander Model\" class=\"wp-image-28\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>McQueen had a background in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tailor\">tailoring</a> before he studied fashion and embarked on a career as a designer. His MA graduation collection caught the attention of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isabella_Blow\">Isabella Blow</a>, who became his patron. McQueen\'s early works gained him recognition as an <em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enfant_terrible\">enfant terrible</a></em> in British fashion, receiving coverage with designs such as the \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bumster\">bumster</a>\" trousers. He became head designer for Givenchy, and in 1999 he formed a partnership with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gucci\">Gucci</a>. A number of his boutiques were established in cities around the world, and his label was expanded to include perfume, fashion accessories and a line of trainers. McQueen\'s catwalk shows were noted for their drama and theatricality, and he was known for his finely-tailored clothes as well as imaginative and sometimes controversial designs. Among his best-known designs are the skull scarf and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armadillo_shoe\">armadillo shoes</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>McQueen died from suicide in 2010 at the age of 40, at his home in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mayfair\">Mayfair</a>, London, shortly after the death of his mother.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":27,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Alexander2-825x1024.jpeg\" alt=\"Alexander Model\" class=\"wp-image-27\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->','Alexander McQueen','','inherit','closed','closed','','18-autosave-v1','','','2022-07-09 09:40:56','2022-07-09 09:40:56','',18,'http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/?p=33',0,'revision','',0),
	(34,1,'2022-07-09 09:41:47','2022-07-09 09:41:47','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Lee Alexander McQueen</strong> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Order_of_the_British_Empire\">CBE</a> (17 March 1969 – 11 February 2010) was a British <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fashion_designer\">fashion designer</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Couturier\">couturier</a>. He founded his own <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_McQueen_(brand)\">Alexander McQueen label</a> in 1992, and was chief designer at <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Givenchy\">Givenchy</a> from 1996 to 2001. His achievements in fashion earned him four <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Designer_of_the_Year\">British Designer of the Year</a> awards (1996, 1997, 2001 and 2003), as well as the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Fashion_Designers_of_America\">CFDA\'s</a> International Designer of the Year award in 2003.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":28,\"sizeSlug\":\"medium\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-medium\"><img src=\"http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Alexander3-300x300.jpeg\" alt=\"Alexander Model\" class=\"wp-image-28\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>McQueen had a background in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tailor\">tailoring</a> before he studied fashion and embarked on a career as a designer. His MA graduation collection caught the attention of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isabella_Blow\">Isabella Blow</a>, who became his patron. McQueen\'s early works gained him recognition as an <em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enfant_terrible\">enfant terrible</a></em> in British fashion, receiving coverage with designs such as the \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bumster\">bumster</a>\" trousers. He became head designer for Givenchy, and in 1999 he formed a partnership with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gucci\">Gucci</a>. A number of his boutiques were established in cities around the world, and his label was expanded to include perfume, fashion accessories and a line of trainers. McQueen\'s catwalk shows were noted for their drama and theatricality, and he was known for his finely-tailored clothes as well as imaginative and sometimes controversial designs. Among his best-known designs are the skull scarf and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armadillo_shoe\">armadillo shoes</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>McQueen died from suicide in 2010 at the age of 40, at his home in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mayfair\">Mayfair</a>, London, shortly after the death of his mother.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":27,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Alexander2-825x1024.jpeg\" alt=\"Alexander Model\" class=\"wp-image-27\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Wikipedia Contributors. “Alexander McQueen.” <em>Wikipedia</em>, Wikimedia Foundation, 7 Dec. 2019, en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_McQueen.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->','Alexander McQueen','','inherit','closed','closed','','18-revision-v1','','','2022-07-09 09:41:47','2022-07-09 09:41:47','',18,'http://localhost/UofF/MMC6145/assignment3-bruner-johnny/?p=34',0,'revision','',0),
